# Netlify Database migrations live here. Files are SQL by default
# (or `.ts` if Drizzle is added later). Filenames must be sortable by
# application order — convention is `0001_name.sql`, `0002_name.sql`,
# etc. Each file is applied exactly once and recorded by the Netlify
# infra; pending vs applied state shows up in `netlify database status`.
#
# This .gitkeep is only here to make the empty directory trackable —
# delete it once a real migration file lands.
